author: Benoît Faucon
title: Iran Expects Oil Exports to Start Rising as Early as Late November
text:
GENEVA—Iran expects to be able to increase its oil exports by 500,000 barrels a day by late November or early December, with sales to Asia rising as a result of the country’s nuclear agreement with global powers, a senior Iranian oil official said on Thursday.
